Package: rufuslinux
Version: 0.1.1
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: parted, dosfstools, ntfs-3g, exfatprogs, rsync, util-linux, policykit-1
Maintainer: Oswaldo Sierra <oswaldox199@gmail.com>
Description: Rufus-like bootable USB creator for Linux
 RufusLinux is a graphical tool for creating bootable USB drives from
 ISO images, mirroring the layout and workflow of the Windows tool Rufus.
 Supports MBR/GPT partitioning, BIOS/UEFI targets, and FAT32/NTFS/exFAT
 filesystems.
